11/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During a TV interview Sunday (10 August), newly-appointed Deputy High Representative in BiH Werner Wendt called for more international assistance to implement reforms.
While stressing that the country's key objective would be to implement EU integration reforms, he also emphasised a series of other important policy targets including refugee returns, education, resolution of Mostar's status, and administration reforms.
He pledged that the Office of the High Representative would continue to provide financial and expert assistance to priority areas.
(BHTV1, BBC - 10/08/03)
